The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Merit Order for squad

Rome: Italys President Giorgio Napolitano announced he would be formally honouring the squad by making them members of the Merit Order of the Republic, even as thousands of Italians gathered on Monday at the Circus Maximus to fete their conquering heroes. 

A deafening roar, fireworks and a sea of flags greeted the teams open-topped bus when, at almost 11 pm local time (2.30 am IST), it finally entered the vast rectangular arena that used to house chariot races. 

The mayors office estimated the crowd at 600,000, with hundreds of thousands more who accompanied the bus in its snails paced progress from a reception at Prime Minister Romano Prodis residence. 

Team coach Marcello Lippi and his players clambered onto a stage and raised the Cup one by one as loudspeakers blared out Italys national anthem and rock group Queens modern-day sporting anthem, We are the Champions. (AGENCIES) 




